post_text:
Port Jeff Village is having a poster contest for anyone interested.
Copied from Trustee Snaden

***CALLING ALL KIDS IN PORT JEFFERSON***

We at Village Hall need your help!

We want to get the message out around town that we would like people in our Village to social distance, wear a mask and wash their hands! We need your help to get that message out. So we are holding a poster contest.

Please gather your paints, crayons, pencils and markers and make a cool sign that will help us let people know how to stay safe and keep others safe as well. These posters will be laminated and put up in the Village.

Please make the posters around 8.5" x 11" size so they will fit in our laminating machine. You can drop them off in our documents box in the back of Village Hall. Please label the back with your name and a way to contact you. Email or cell number is best. And have fun creating some very important and helpful artwork!🎨✂️🖌🖍✏️

Happy March 1st, Parents!! For those of you with kiddos at Scraggy...

Today kicks off our SCRAGGY BOOSTERTHON!! Unlike last year where they did a “fun run”, this year we chose a Fitness Challenge!

Register your child at Funrun.com
Choose Edna Louise Spear Elementary School.

Upload your child’s picture to the superhero video (if you want to) and share it with the people you love most!

Super easy and fun fundraiser! This year’s theme is STEM related. Watch the video for more info!!

You are welcome to join us on Tuesday 3/19 to watch your child in the fitness challenge. We will post the schedule ASAP.

Thank you for all your support!!!

post_text:
💥The PTA has requested to make a Science Week...and it was approved!💥
💥Have your child bring in their projects on Friday March 22nd (either with them to school or parents can drop off until 4pm that day). Each participant will get to display their projects in their classroom for a few days & have the opportunity to explain to their friends what their project is about. 💥The Science fair takes place on Wednesday the 27th. Check out the Virtual Backpack for all information before your little scientist gets started.
💥We are also kicking the week off with “The Wacky Science Guy” assembly & ending the week with “The Physics Experience” assembly. It should be a lot of fun for the kids!!💥
💥We also can use some help, so please let us know if you would like to, thanks 💥

post_text:
Calling all ES Parents:
A message From the 5th Grade Committee

This year we decided to bring back the square one art fundraiser to help support the fifth-grade committee!! This is a favorite by many parents as it’s a great opportunity to help boost your child’s confidence by purchasing their artwork as well as creating a keepsake that lasts a lifetime! There are many options available to purchase. And it’s a great time of year as all of the items should be delivered before the holiday break. Think of purchasing for yourselves as well as Grandparents, Aunt’s, Uncle’s, anyone who is special to your child! Please take this opportunity to order the artwork as the originals will not be sent home. Orders can be placed online or submitted to us by the deadline which is November 20th. I know the children worked hard on these so let’s show them our support!! If you have any questions feel free to reach out.

Catalogs were sent home today.
Three ways to place an order
Online
Paper order form
Phone orders
Must Order by 11/20

post_text: FYI
shared_text:
Port Jefferson School District
August 17, 2018 at 3:53 PM ·

LIPA update - Aug. 17

Statement From the Port Jefferson School District

Earlier this week, the New York State Supreme Court ruled against the Port Jefferson School District’s claim that LIPA breached its promises to never seek a reduction of the assessed valuation of the Port Jefferson power plant. This decision, which follows a nearly four year process, now allows LIPA to go to trial against the Town Of Brookhaven, the assessing authority, and seek dramatic reductions in the taxes it pays to the school district for the plant. While this decision is not the outcome the district was hoping for, we vow to continue to explore our options as we work to protect our school district's financial future and the needs of our community. The district will work to keep the community apprised of any updates on the matter.

post_text:
From the BOOSTERTHON ladies: We love Scraggy Hill School!! Our Fun Run is TODAY!! In our huddles yesterday we learned all about creativity. Ethan tells us that creativity means using our imagination and thinking outside the box to help us solve problems.

We got 'pied in the face' by Mrs. Santini’s class and Mr. Orlowski’s class. The students loved it and the teachers were in shock!

We also were able to pop into Mr. Orlowski’s class and spend some time with his wonderful students! It was so nice to give them some one-on-one special attention.

We have loved being able to form a relationship with the students and the staff. We are truly going to miss you all but we cannot wait to celebrate tomorrow with everyone!

post_text:
From Mojo JoJo & Ninja Nicole: Hey there Awesome Scraggy Hill Team!! Today was so much fun! The students energy and enthusiasm motivates us all day long! In our huddles today, we learned all about trustworthiness. Ethan tells us that trustworthiness means being a good friend and keeping our promises. We explained to the students that they make 3 promises every day when they come to school:
1. To try their best
2. To listen to their teacher and
3. To be kind to their classmates!
And that it was their job to keep those promises!!!

We are so excited to be celebrating each students hard work from the past two weeks! If you have not registered on Funrun.com yet now is the perfect time to do so. Thank you for all of your support so far, we cannot do this without you! Tonight the students have a very exciting challenge (from a very special room) in store! Check out the video message below to find out what it is.
Video Link: https://vimeo.com/266555329
